         <abstract>
            <p>An algorithm for a generalized Chebyshev interpolation procedure, increasing the number of sample points more moderately than doubling, is presented. The FFT for a real sequence is incorporated into the algorithm to enhance its efficiency. Numerical comparison with other existing algorithms is given.</p>
          </abstract>
